      -------------------------------------------------------------------
       Naming convention for variadic and array-based function variants
      -------------------------------------------------------------------


1. Overview
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Functions that accept a variable number of arguments follow a consistent naming
convention based on two dimensions:

  * Argument structure -- whether the function takes raw key/value pairs or
    otelc_kv structs.

  * Multiplicity mechanism -- whether multiple items are passed as a variadic
    NULL-terminated argument list, an array with an explicit count, or a
    va_list.


2. Suffix conventions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  _var     Variadic (NULL-terminated).  The function takes one or more leading
           arguments of the item type, followed by additional items of the same
           type as variadic arguments, terminated by NULL.

  _kv_var  Variadic of otelc_kv structs (NULL-terminated).  Same as _var, but
           each variadic argument is a pointer to an otelc_kv struct rather
           than raw key/value pairs.

  _kv_n    Array with explicit count.  The function takes a pointer to an array
           of otelc_kv structs and a size_t length parameter.

  _v       va_list variant (internal).  Mirrors a variadic function but accepts
           a va_list instead of "...".  Follows the C standard library
           convention (printf/vprintf, sprintf/vsprintf).

  (none)   Printf-style variadic functions that take a format string followed
           by "..." receive no special suffix.


3. Span API function families
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The span API demonstrates all three public variants for each operation:

  set_baggage:

    set_baggage_var(span, key, value, ...)
    set_baggage_kv_var(span, kv, ...)
    set_baggage_kv_n(span, kv, kv_len)

  set_attribute:

    set_attribute_var(span, key, value, ...)
    set_attribute_kv_var(span, kv, ...)
    set_attribute_kv_n(span, kv, kv_len)

  add_event:

    add_event_var(span, name, ts, key, value, ...)
    add_event_kv_var(span, name, ts, kv, ...)
    add_event_kv_n(span, name, ts, kv, kv_len)

  get_baggage:

    get_baggage_var(span, key, ...)

The _var variants accept raw key/value pairs as alternating arguments.  The
_kv_var variants accept otelc_kv struct pointers.  The _kv_n variants accept
a fixed-size array with a count parameter.


4. Internal va_list variants
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Internal (static) helper functions use the _v suffix to accept a va_list,
allowing the variadic public function to delegate parsing:

  yaml_get_node(...)    ->  yaml_get_node_v(..., va_list ap)
  otel_logger_log(...)  ->  otel_logger_log_v(..., va_list ap)

Both the logger and the YAML module use the _v suffix, consistent with the
examples above.


5. Printf-style variadic functions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Functions that accept a printf-style format string followed by variadic
arguments receive no naming suffix:

  otelc_sprintf(char **ret, const char *format, ...)
  logger->ops->log(..., const char *format, ...)
  logger->ops->log_span(..., const char *format, ...)


6. Parameter naming for otelc_kv arrays
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

When a function accepts an otelc_kv pointer (with or without a count), the
parameters must be named kv and kv_len:

  const struct otelc_kv *kv, size_t kv_len

This applies uniformly across the span interface: set_baggage_kv_n,
set_attribute_kv_n, add_event_kv_n, add_link, and record_exception all use
kv/kv_len.

The logger interface uses attr/attr_len for its key-value array parameters.
This is acceptable because the logger operates in a different domain (log
record attributes) and is internally consistent.


7. Summary table
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Pattern              Suffix    Last parameters
  -------------------  --------  --------------------------
  Raw key/value pairs  _var      ..., key, value, ..., NULL
  otelc_kv structs     _kv_var   ..., kv, ..., NULL
  Array + count        _kv_n     ..., kv, kv_len
  va_list helper       _v        ..., va_list ap
  Printf-style         (none)    ..., format, ...
